2026-04-07 14:45:00 [DEBUG] openai._base_client: Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/chat/completions', 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-85b4f892-13f5-44be-b857-0fba117d2e02', 'content': None, 'json_data': {'messages': [{'role': 'system', 'content': '你是一位风扇噪声领域的学术专家。请分析以下论文的标题和摘要，返回JSON格式的分析结果。\n\nJSON结构要求：\n{\n  "summary": "中文综述（150-300字），概括论文核心内容",\n  "methods": "研究方法（中文，100-200字），说明使用的关键研究方法",\n  "innovations": "创新点（中文，列出主要创新贡献）",\n  "conclusions": "结论（中文，总结主要结论）",\n  "relevance_score": 8,\n  "keywords": ["keyword1", "keyword2", "keyword3"]\n}\n\nrelevance_score评分标准（1-10）：\n10: 直接研究风扇噪声\n8-9: 与风扇噪声高度相关（如气动声学、叶轮机械噪声）\n5-7: 有一定相关性（如通用声学方法）\n1-4: 弱相关\n\n请严格返回JSON格式，不要添加其他内容。'}, {'role': 'user', 'content': '论文标题：FAN AND INTAKE COUPLED AERODYNAMIC DESIGN OPTIMIZATION FOR UHBR AERO-ENGINES WITH LOW-PRESSURE RATIO FANS\n\n论文摘要：To reduce fuel consumption as well as noise and CO2 emissions, the overall trend in civil aviation is to decrease&#13;\\nexhaust velocities associated with an increase of the fan diameter, implying more weight and more drag because of&#13;\\nthe larger nacelle size. To compensate for the introduced weight increase, the concept of nacelles with short inlet,&#13;\\nfor which the interaction between the nacelle and the fan is higher than for current engines, is often considered. This&#13;\\npaper proposes to design a short inlet geometry with a length over diameter ratio of l/D�0.35 that provides better or&#13;\\nequal aerodynamic performances, predominantly for the fan, than conventional long inlet configurations with typical&#13;\\nratios of l/D�0.65. To obtain such a design, an optimization process with a flow field covering the entire fan, intake&#13;\\nand nacelle system is used. The first step is to define the parameterization of the nacelle which finally contains&#13;\\nthe nacelle and the intake contour as basics parameters. The next step is to establish a robust and automatic&#13;\\nmeshing procedure of the entire calculation domain (far field, nacelle, intake and fan), which guarantees a high&#13;\\nmesh quality independent of the parameter selected. AutoOpti, which is an optimization tool developed at DLR,&#13;\\nis applied, providing an optimization framework based on an evolutionary algorithm with heavy surrogate model&#13;\\nenhancements. For the calculations, which are realized with the DLR in-house solver TRACE, three operating&#13;\\nconditions are considered: static take-off (OP1), take-off (OP2) and cruise (OP3). The classification of the results&#13;\\nis based on the assessment of the fan aerodynamic performances, considering fan total pressure ratio for OP1&#13;\\nand OP2 with the aim to increase the fan stability limit and on the isentropic efficiency for OP3. Among the Paretofront,&#13;\\nthe best individual is selected and analyzed qualitatively and quantitatively, explaining the performance gain&#13;\\nand corresponding geometric modifications of the intake and lip section. A new optimization process is realized to&#13;\\nminimize the pressure peak observed at static take-off condition on the nacelle’s leading edge. Then, a full annulus&#13;\\nnacelle geometry is created in order to study the influence of some asymmetric parameters such as the angle of&#13;\\nthe nacelle inlet face (droop angle), the thickness in circumferential direction and the inflow angle'}], 'model': 'deepseek-chat', 'max_tokens': 1500, 'response_format': {'type': 'json_object'}, 'temperature': 0.2}}
