 of transonic performance. Starting with a datum inlet (+6° scarf), this paper describes the effect of lip shaping on scarfed (-20°) intakes at high speed (Mach 0.8 & 0.85). An encouraging equivalence has been achieved between the datum and scarfed intake and further detailed work (internal surfaces) eventually leading to experiments has been recommended. Avenues for related future work are noted e.g. on scarf angle optimisation. NOMENCLATURE'}], 'model': 'deepseek-chat', 'max_tokens': 1500, 'response_format': {'type': 'json_object'}, 'temperature': 0.2}}
