ise propagation and radiation using an axisymmetric but otherwise realistic geometry. Seven potential sources of error, associated with the part-span approximation, are identified and categorised into three characteristics: source truncation error, in-duct propagation error, and far-field radiation error. Part II of this study, reported separately, extends the current work to high-amplitude non-linear propagation.'}], 'model': 'deepseek-chat', 'max_tokens': 1500, 'response_format': {'type': 'json_object'}, 'temperature': 0.2}}
