 on the different requirements of aerodynamic and aeroelastic fan analyses, quasi-3D and 3D rotor models were used to determine the accuracy and computational cost reduction achieved with the PSpTM model. For aerodynamic analyses, a speed-up factor of up to 8 was obtained concerning the BDF2 method. Depending on the accuracy required, speedup factors of around 2–6 can be achieved for unsteady aeroelastic and aeroacoustic analyses.'}], 'model': 'deepseek-chat', 'max_tokens': 1500, 'response_format': {'type': 'json_object'}, 'temperature': 0.2}}
