ation with an elongated straight duct demonstrates weak coupling to loading conditions concerning sound power and roughness. An overall consistent scaling of aerodynamic and acoustic performance is observed for the parallel fan system when compared to the single fan case, irrespective of inlet geometry. Sound quality estimates of two incoherent sound sources agree well with measured values of the parallel fan system, apart from fluctuation strength, which is overestimated at stall conditions. • Bell-mouth shaped inlets can lead to increased sound power for rotating ring fans. • Psychoacoustics of axial fans at high loads can be favored with straight duct inlets. • Acoustics of axial parallel fan systems can be described as incoherent fan sources.'}], 'model': 'deepseek-chat', 'max_tokens': 1500, 'response_format': {'type': 'json_object'}, 'temperature': 0.2}}
