B(A) and 19.6 dB(A), respectively. The toroidal propeller significantly reduced noise while improving aerodynamic performance. This study provides a theoretical basis, experimental methods, and data support for the aerodynamic and noise calculations of toroidal propellers. It has significant engineering implications for the development of low-noise propellers for drones.'}], 'model': 'deepseek-chat', 'max_tokens': 1500, 'response_format': {'type': 'json_object'}, 'temperature': 0.2}}
