orous leading edges are more effective for the reduction of the tonal noise. For the poro-wavy leading edges, both the tonal noise and broadband noise are significantly reduced, which means that the combined poro-wavy leading edges possess both the advantages of the wavy and porous treatments. The underlying flow mechanisms responsible for the noise reduction are finally analyzed in detail.'}], 'model': 'deepseek-chat', 'max_tokens': 1500, 'response_format': {'type': 'json_object'}, 'temperature': 0.2}}
