pressure levels inside the intake. It is anticipated that the sound amplification is attributed to the distortion associated with the intake lip geometry, intake length, and crosswind speed. Non-dimensional total pressure distribution revealed the high correlation between the fan noise and the inlet distortion.'}], 'model': 'deepseek-chat', 'max_tokens': 1500, 'response_format': {'type': 'json_object'}, 'temperature': 0.2}}
