rf and scoop aero-intakes (2007)\n8. SILENCE(R): A major step towards aircraft noise reduction (2008) - From 2001 up to 2007, SILENCE(R) has focused on the development of aircraft noise reduction technologies. As an European Union project coordinated by ...\n9. Computational modelling of acoustic scattering from a cylindrical duct with a rotor into uniform mean flow (2006) - The paper presents a computational study of acoustic scattering from a cylindrical duct into uniform flow. The sound source is a fan inside the duct r...\n10. 3D parallel spectral computations of fan noise (2006) - A three-dimensional computational aeroacoustics code has been developed for the simulation of tone noise generated by turbofan engine inlets. The code...'}], 'model': 'deepseek-chat', 'max_tokens': 800, 'temperature': 0.3}}
